418→Key implementation methods for `PromptLoader`:
419→
420→- `new(forge_dir: PathBuf) -> Self` -- stores the forge dir path
421→- `prompt_file_path(&self, specialist: &SpecialistType) -> PathBuf` -- returns `{forge_dir}/autoresearch/prompts/{agent_name}.md`
422→- `load_specialist_prompt(&self, specialist: &SpecialistType) -> PromptConfig` -- tries file, falls back to default
423→- `load_from_file(path: &Path, specialist: &SpecialistType) -> Option<PromptConfig>` -- parses frontmatter + body, returns None on any error
424→- `build_default_config(specialist: &SpecialistType) -> PromptConfig` -- constructs from hardcoded data
425→
426→**Frontmatter parsing logic:**
427→1. Check if file content starts with `---`
428→2. Find the closing `---` (second occurrence)
429→3. Parse the content between them as YAML into `PromptFrontmatter`
430→4. Everything after the closing `---` is the body
431→
432→**Focus area extraction from body:**
433→1. Find `## Focus Areas` section in the body
434→2. Parse bullet points (`- `) until the next `##` heading or end of file
435→3. If no Focus Areas section found, fall back to `SpecialistType::focus_areas()`
436→
437→**Default config construction:**
438→Use `SpecialistType::display_name()`, `SpecialistType::focus_areas()`, and `SpecialistType::default_gating()` to construct a `PromptConfig` with a body matching the current hardcoded template from `build_review_prompt()` in `dispatcher.rs` (the Role, Focus Areas, Instructions, Output Format sections).
